HEADWORD: Counterfort
<hw>Coun"ter*fort`</hw> <pr>(-f?rt`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A kind of buttress of masonry to strengthen a
revetment wall.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A spur or projection of a mountain.</def>
<rj><au>Imp. Dict.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Countergage</ent>⟦br⟧
